<br>
Grab about 300pp and sit your arse down in the bank of Thurgadin.<br>
<br>
Buy Medium jar sketches, water flasks and blocks of clay.  Combine on pottery wheel until trivial is hit. Destroy all completed items, they are not worth finishing. (around 40). [You can buy from vendors in the bank]<br>
<br>
After you hit trivial buy medium bowl sketches, water flasks and blocks of clay.  Combine on pottery wheel until trivial is hit (about 122).  Destroy all completed items, they are not worth finishing. [This will take a good 4 hours]<br>
<br>
You can make some large bowls after this, but they are way more expensive.  Destroy all completed items, they are not worth finishing.  (I took pottery to 126 but it cost me 100pp for about 4 points of skill raise).<br>
<br>
Now what to do?  You need to go and farm a few items.  Two good places to farm are going to be Velks and Crystal Caverns.  CC is best since it is so much easier, but the drops seem to be more frequent in Velks.<br>
<br>
What to get:<br>
<br>
Crystalline Silk<br>
Small bricks of Velium<br>
Small pieces of Velium<br>
<br>
You can buy this stuff, but way expensive in bazaar.  Kill miners in CC or Spiders in Velks.  BTW bricks don’t stack.<br>
<br>
Combine the following on the pottery wheel (don’t stack items on the wheel):  3 Silks, 2 glass shards and one small brick of velium = unrefined velious vial.<br>
<br>
Now combine the unrefined velious vial and a high quality firing sheet (same vendor in bank has this) and you get: Velious Vial.  Make many of these as possible since your end result will be LORE!!!<br>
<br>
Last step:  Go see Frundle Frenkler (she is across from the Pally guild in Thurgadin) and say “what velium vapor?” and make sure you have an open inventory slot.  You will get something called a purifier box from her.<br>
<br>
Combine the following in the purifier box (don’t stack):  2 small pieces of velium and one velium vial.  Do it in front of her and get another purifier box when done (it will poof once you combine).  Now you have a VIAL OF VELIUM VAPORS and you are ready to make another to put in the bank or keep on hand for making later.<br>
<br>
Vial of Velium Vapors<br>
Magic Item Lore Item No Drop<br>
Effect: Thurgadin Gate<br>
All/All<br>
10 second cast<br>
<br>
Way worth the trouble!<br>
<br>
Thanks Baronnx for the info!<br>
<br>
Hikmer<br>
